30418:
30 TES Strips:
Wels                      Reagents
1       Sample well.
2-3-4   Empty wells.
5       Conjugate: Alkaline phosphatase-labeled testosterone derivative + calf serum + gelatine 
(porcine) + releasing agent
6       Empty well.
7-8     Wash buffer: Tris-NaCl (0.05 mol/l) pH 7.4 + 0.9 g/l sodium azide (600μl).
9       Wash buffer: diethanolamine (1.1 mol/l or 11.5%) pH 9.8
10      Reading cuvette with substrate: 4-Methyl-umbelliferyl-phosphate (0.6 mmol/l) + 
diethanolamine (DEA) (0.62 mol/l or 6.6%) pH 9.2
30 TES SPRs:
SPRs sensitized with polyclonal anti-testosterone immunoglobulins (rabbit).
TES control:
Human serum + testosterone
TES calibrator:
Human serum + testosterone
MLE card
Specifications sheet containing the factory master calibration data required to calibrate the test.
